   Flaunting a gymnasium, football pitch, basketball court, lawn tennis court, volleyball court, chess games, barbecue spot, laundry, lounge, supermarket and children’s playground, among others, the promoters said there are plans already to make the basketball competition a quarterly event. 
   
The next edition, scheduled for August, promises to be more exciting and bigger. The August edition will feature an increase in the number of participating teams from 10 to 16 teams.
   
The Ecofitness Hub is open to the public daily for fitness enthusiasts willing to step up their fitness routine.